nts1.d: A monthly transmission of displaced rock n roll, exotic punk and early electronics, paying favor to all things primitive and sleazy. LA visual artist Amanda Siegel delves into the international underground, offering a thorough sonic survey of protopunk, hard rock, synthpunk, powerpop, psych, industrial and more.

nts1.d: Festive hip hop from Gucci Mane, Lil B, Tyler The Creator, Bladee and more.

Raj Chaudhuri - aka Raji Rags. NTS since day one. Always eclectic, never boring. Raj rustles up a seamless monthly mix that journeys through the BPMs.
From the host: "Favourite records of 2025. Three hours. Live in the mix."
Iconic queer party crew Adonis showcase their residents on a monthly rotation live from the London studio.

Waya Fyam dives into Nairobi’s wild soundscape – shrap bars, kapuka, and dancehall riddims. Mixing these with moombahton, a Dutch-born sound built on the same Caribbean grooves, to show how Kenyan street energy links up with global club culture. Expect heavy bass, raw slang, and pure movement.
From the host: "As we close off the year, I take time to reflect on where I started as a DJ, this is an archive from my first show which was a B2B from TulzTelzzzzZZ. 2025may have come with losses, or wins for some of you,: but what's important is that we made it through 2025! I am proud of you and happy holidays!"

nts1.n: Autotune the World w/ Christopher Kirkley (R)
nts1.d: International portal for contemporary pop, leaning into the autotuned future… from the mind of Christopher Kirkley, the mastermind behind record label Sahel Sounds.

Martha is a DJ and broadcaster from South London with roots in community radio and documentary making. Each of Martha’s thoughtfully curated radio shows navigate the fringes of electronic music, with a clear narrative that is grounded in community and storytelling.

nts2.d:
Welcome to LXXXVIII – the ninth Actress album to be created by Darren Cunningham and the very first presentation of Actress’ voyage into luxury sonics.
A lifetime in the making, LXXXVIII is the culmination of 25 years’ honing mind-shorting, soul-igniting audio
infusions for dance floors, rave dens, festivals, and concert hall, and the inaugural vessel for Actress’ cruise into novel strata of artistic influence: the executive suites, yacht decks and private jets of our planet’s ultimate power players.

nts2.n: VIBRATIONS FOR A BETTER WORLD W/ AOKI TAKAMASA (R)

nts2.d:
From his very first hit as barely a teenager – the energetic, improvised "Fingertips (Part. 2)" to his classic run in the mid-70s, winning three Best Album Grammys in almost as many years, to his status today as a living giant of popular music, there is perhaps no better ambassador for the life-changing joy of music alive today than Stevie Wonder. 
Suncut picks out two hours of classics and deep cuts from the storied career of a soul, R&B, and pop icon.
Guitar music, electronic musings and heady explorations with Baba Stiltz.
Leaf through songwriter Calvin LeCompte’s monthly selection via The Uline Catalog…

nts2.n: CREEP ZONE: Christmas Special w/ Zach Malm
nts2.d:
Stones Throw's James Pants joins forces with Marc Schaller for an hour-long dive into dreamy electronics, wired sounds and experimentation.
From the host: "Zach and I were roommates in uni, and on day one discovered we both shared huge record collections. At the time I was mostly hip-hop, soul, jazz, and Zach was like Slint, Rodan, Tortoise. Definitely cooler. We've been friends ever since. He is now the deepest XMAS collector I know. Here's his mix."
A monthly hour from Jane Records label-runner Braden Wells.

subtle.d: XOSÉ is a DJ and aspiring producer mixing and making mostly UK Garage, Grime and UK Funky. FORWARD PRESSURE largely focuses on the aforementioned UK born genres, though you can expect a variety of UK influenced sounds.

Sempra is a producer & DJ based in London, specialising in the fusion of UK Garage, Jungle and Breakbeat with dreamy vocal melodies and the beautiful instrumentation found in Soul and contemporary RnB. Sempra’s consistent output has been released by labels such as Future Classic and Headroom, gaining industry support from the likes of Nia Archives, Sherelle, Yung Singh and Dr Dubplate.

Cicely is a northern raised London based music photographer and DJ. From learning to mix during lockdown, she has since played at clubs across the country in venues such as Fabric, Corsica and Fold.

Cicely runs a collective and events night under the name NRG CRU which focus heavily on the high energy rave sound. She is highly influenced by the northern sound she grew up with, and you can hear this within her sets. Expect heavy blends of techno and hardcore while she shines the light on her favourite northern artists.

Live & Direct is the show that promises to make you dance and make you laugh, with your fave tunes that make you go 'Rahhh ain't hear this in time' and all the cheesy jokes from me, Hannah :) Lock in for the sickest guests and the most relatable stories about daily slips and hilarious situations I find myself in.

Bristol-born and London-based, Not Bad For A Girl resident DaiSu has been involved in the music scene since 2018 and has featured on stations such as Radio 1 Dance, BBC 6 Music and Melodic Distraction, as well as playing on line ups for Keep Hush, Skiddle and Red Bull. Her penchant for bass, breaks and 2-step has landed her gigs supporting acts such as Interplanetary Criminal, Main Phase, Craigie Knowes and Big Ang. In September 2022, her debut EP ‘Lightwork’ was released with Gather Records and was featured in DJ Mag's staff picks that same month.

Vinyl DJ from Leigh-on-Sea. Loves collecting records with a wide array of taste ranging from House and Techno to Grime, Dubstep and Jungle. Garage holds a special place in his heart and makes up the largest part of my collection and DJ sets.

DJ & Producer hailing from Watford influenced by Hip-Hop, Dubstep, Grime with releases on NSX records & Ghost Phone, spinning electronic genres from R&B edits, Drum and Bass and everything in between.
Highlander brings you 2 hours of the freshest Jungle, Hardcore, Dubstep and Breaks. 3rd Saturday 7-9pm lock in!

subtle.n: What's The Weather, Selecta? w/ Megan Wroe

subtle.d:
Hailing from Mumbai, now living in London, Chaitu is energised by the UK sound and scene.

With a love of all things weird, weighty and groovy; his mixes and productions bridge electro, techno, breaks, UKG and Jungle, with sprinklings of everything in between.

Chaitu champions provocative beats that break down the barriers of style, genre and expectation, all while keeping you moving.

Saraphim (aka RNS & RDubz) are two Essex based Producer/DJ’s currently focused on Dubstep & the 140 spectrum, mixing ethnical and grime influences into their music. You can expect anything from deep and melodic meditative vibes to high energy driven music.
London based DJ who enjoys exploring the darker, bassier corners of Jungle, Breaks, Techno and Drum & Bass, especially when it is laced with a bit of acid.

Wheel2Wheel is a Manchester based event which primarily focuses on the underground sectors to genres such as UK Garage, House, Tech House, Electro, Minimal and Breakbeat. Co-Founder Freddie SJ hosts the first hour of the show, sharing his favourites as well as recent digs across the genres, and then invites fellow friends, artists and nights from the scene to present hour-long guest mixes which aims to shine a light on their sound and who they are!


With hours of Discogs screen-time under his belt and a passion for 90's & early 00's releases, expect to hear a variety of different tunes from Labels you may have never heard of and Countries you might not expect!


Give us a follow on Instagram to hear about our upcoming events and all other things music related! @wheel2wheel.mcr

subtle.d: Japanese DJ from Tokyo, currently living in London.  Based on UK club music, but straddles other genres such as dancehall, reggaeton, gqom and amapiano.
